column5: Required data item for all claims to facilitate reporting of routine information and adjudication of claims (i.e., are services appropriate given the diagnosis?)
The NCoD is mapped to the WHO's International Classification of Diseases, version 10 (ICD-10). ICD-10 is the most widely recognized coding of diagnoses worldwide.

For health centers and primary hospitals, it is recommended that the Mini-NCoD is used to populate the concept set for Diagnosis. Facilities have already been train on this concept set and are switching to using the NCoD codes and diagnosis names for HMIS reporting as the transition to DHIS2.
